text: Arotrophora chionaula is a moth of the family Tortricidae. It is known from Australia. ==Taxonomy== Arotrophora chionaula is the original combination. However, it is known to be misplaced in this genus, but has not been assigned to another genus yet. ==References== Category:Archipini Category:Taxa named by Edward Meyrick Category:Taxa named by Alexey Diakonoff
title: Arotrophora chionaula
